go are hundreds of deg$^2$, WFST is expected to find\n$\\sim$30\\% kilonovae in the first two nights during O4 period.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2023 05:08:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 25 Mar 2023 05:26:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 23 Apr 2023 03:39:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-25"}
